## 03 — UI/UX (Draft)

### UX principles (from `docs/06-UI-UX-BLUEPRINT.md`)
- Consistent layout + navigation across routes
- Clear loading + error + empty states
- Mobile-first responsiveness
- Fast “happy path” interactions: like, bookmark, subscribe, tip, unlock

### Key missing UX categories to validate/complete
- Discovery:
  - tags/hashtags UX (attach tags on create, browse by tag, trending tags)
  - category browsing consistency
- Monetization UX:
  - subscription management page (cancel/renew/history)
  - PPV library / purchase history
  - creator earnings breakdown: subscriptions vs ppv vs tips
  - bundles store UX (creator sells bundles, fan purchases, library)
- Live:
  - live list page
  - stream detail page (paywall gating)
  - “go live” creator flow (Mux Live)
- Notifications:
  - web push opt-in UI, preferences, graceful fallback

### Navigation consistency requirement
- AppShell should wrap all in-app and public pages that require consistent top/bottom nav.
- Any route group bypassing the layout must have a `layout.tsx` wrapper.

